===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|regretten|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|regreter|lang=fro}}, {{term|regrater||to lament|lang=fro}}, from {{term|re-|pos=intensive prefix|lang=fro}} + {{m|fro|*greter}}, {{m|fro|*grater||to weep}}, from Old {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*gretan|*grētan}} {{gloss|"to weep, mourn, lament"; from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*grētaną||to weep}}}}, and Old {{etyl|frk|en}} {{m|frk|*greotan|*grēotan|to cry, weep}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*greutaną||to weep, cry}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ghrew-||to weep, be sad}}, equivalent to {{prefix|re|greet|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{m|goh|grāzan||to cry}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|grǣtan||to weep, greet}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|grēotan||to weep, lament}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|gráta||to weep, groan|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐌲𐍂𐌴𐍄𐌰𐌽||to weep|tr=gretan|lang=got|sc=Goth}}. More at {{term|greet|lang=en}}.

